The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The problem studied is a variant of the generalized assignment problem (GAP), which is a well-known problem in combinatorial optimization (cs.DS). The paper proposes algorithms for solving the problem, which involves optimization and decision-making, and thus falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also involves information theory, as it deals with certifying that no agent can benefit from hiding its compatibility with items, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
